WDP is a significant, established 59-acre distribution park approximately 5 miles south of junction 15 of the M40 motorway providing fast access to the national motorway network via the recently upgraded A429.

Situated to the west of Wellesbourne, immediately adjoining to the A429 at its junction with the B4086 Stratford Road, the park benefits from excellent frontage to the A429.

With excellent transport communications, the Birmingham to London Marylebone (Chiltern) railway line is accessible from Warwick Parkway, Warwick and Leamington Spa railway stations.

The property is situated at Swift Valley, Rugby, a prime industrial and distribution location within the heart of the Golden Triangle. Access to Junction 1 of the M6 is 2 miles to the north, providing direct connectivity to the region’s motorway network. Swift Valley is located 2 miles north of Rugby town centre and within easy walking distance of the local amenities at Elliot’s Fields and Junction One Retail Park. Existing Swift Valley occupiers include DHL, Amazon, Hermes, Britvic, Coates and Cummins, to name a few.

 Swift 34 is a modern, high quality industrial / distribution unit which has been comprehensively refurbished. The warehouse includes a dedicated loading bay, together with works office and a staff welfare area at the rear. The front elevation comprises two-storey offices with reception, kitchen and WC’s. Externally, there is a large fenced yard and dedicated car park.
